 sociology and ethnography, folklore studies, palaeography and socio-historical linguistics. They range from the early modern Hispanic Empire to twentieth-century Australia, including studies of modern Britain, Iceland, Finland, Italy, Germany, South Africa and the USA. The book demonstrates the importance of studying manuscript culture to give a voice, a presence and dignity to the ordinary protagonists of history.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Jun 2024) 0aWorking class authorsxHistory and criticism. 7aHISTORY / Social History.2bisacsh1 aAshplant, T. G., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aElspaß, Stephan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGerber, David A., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGómez, Antonio Castillo, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKing, Steven, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLyons, Martyn, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLyons, Martyn, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aMagnússon, Sigurður Gylfi, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMoss, David, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSalmi-Niklander, Kirsti, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSchechter, Brandon M., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aStanley, Liz, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aTurunen, Risto, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aÓlafsson, Davíð, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertManchester University Press 2023 eBook-Packagez9783111206455o